      "span_text": "Interestingly, a single isolate of H. haemolyticus with N526K also had the L389F substitution, which has been associated with higher levels of b-lactam resistance (especially to cephalosporins) when seen in conjunction with S385T in H. influenzae (termed group III). [CITATION_1]"
